The article is a transcript of a conference call briefing on President Obama's upcoming trip to Africa. The purpose of the trip is to advance U.S. interests in Africa, which is seen as one of the most important emerging regions in the world. The trip will focus on trade and investment, economic opportunities, democracy, and the empowerment of young people. The President will visit Senegal, South Africa, and Tanzania, and will engage with leaders from these countries as well as members of the private sector and civil society. The trip aims to strengthen U.S. engagement and leadership in Africa and promote African economic growth, democratic progress, and peace and security.